2. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The Hamilton-Ostrogradsky principle is used as a criterion for searching an optimal control, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
3. cs.ME (Mechanical Engineering): The paper deals with the motion of a flexible object, which is a topic of interest in mechanical engineering. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper may involve computational methods for optimizing the motion of the flexible object.
